<TITLE> Police question Tarique at jail gate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 4 (bdnews24.com)  Police interrogated Friday Tarique Rahman, elder son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia, at the Dhaka Central Jail gate. Investigation officers of Gulshan and Dhanmondi police stations questioned him in two extortion cases. Deputy inspector general, prisons, Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com that Tarique was interrogated from 12pm to 3:15pm, excluding the period of Friday prayers. Sub-inspector of Gulshan Police Station Imtiaz Hossain told bdnews24.com that he questioned Tarique for about one and a half hours in the Tk 1.32 crore extortion case filed by businessman Khan Md Aftabuddin on Mar 27, 2007. "We may have to question him further, if needed," Imtiaz said. Dhanmondi Police Station sub-inspector Kazi Mainul questioned Tarique for about an hour on the Tk 53 lakh extortion case filed by contractor Mir Zahir Hossain on Apr 1, 2007. bdnews24.com/
